rComments: Unfortunately we no longer have this fella as a professor. He was a in-the-field practitioner and knew his stuff really well. He got sick of all of the crybabies wanting A's and left.

A true gentleman and he obviously cares about his students. A good sense of humour and he knows his stuff. A practitioner so you'll get in the trenches knowledge. Good life stories on how he actually applied certain aspects of the course.

Funny, kind, clear and a lot of first hand knowledge. Its clear he's used to teaching at the undergrad level though, so moves slower than necessary through material, which can get dull. The exam was fair though ,and I really learned a lot. Couldn't ask for a nicer or more dedicated prof. Also, he's a bit of a silver fox!
